cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with adversarial attacks on object detection models, specifically face detectors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel strategy using a neural network-based constrained optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the attack against a JPEG compression-based defense, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates the attack on the 300-W face dataset, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
